cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with medical image segmentation using CT scans. The use of an end-to-end network with generative and discriminative modules suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. The mention of multi-phase information and collaboration between phases suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks for segmentation suggests that it may also belong to the neural and evolutionary computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
